## 8. DON'T (Anti-patterns)

#### 8.1. Contrast Mistakes
- âŒ **Ignoring WCAG**: Don't skip contrast testing
- âŒ **Pure black** `oklch(0% 0 0)` for backgrounds â€” causes harsh contrast and eye strain
- âŒ **Pure white** `oklch(100% 0 0)` for text in dark mode â€” too bright
- âŒ **Pure white on pure black** without good reason â€” causes discomfort
- âŒ **Low contrast text**: Don't use light gray on white
- âŒ **Color-only links**: Don't remove underlines without alternative
- âŒ **Insufficient UI contrast**: Don't use subtle borders/dividers

### 8.2. Color System Mistakes
- âŒ **Too many colors**: Don't create rainbow interfaces
- âŒ **Inconsistent usage**: Don't use colors arbitrarily
- âŒ **No semantic meaning**: Don't make red mean "success"
- âŒ **Pure colors**: Don't use fully saturated colors everywhere

### 8.3. Saturation Mistakes
- âŒ **High saturation (C > 0.35)** for large areas in dark mode: Creates visual vibration effect
- âŒ **Very high saturated colors (C > 0.40)** for backgrounds in any mode: Causes eye strain and reduces readability
- âŒ **Zero saturation (C = 0)** for accent colors: Loses color identity and makes accents indistinguishable from grays

### 8.4. Dark Mode Mistakes
- âŒ **Pure black backgrounds**: Causes eye strain â€” use dark grays
- âŒ **Pure white text**: Too harsh on dark backgrounds â€” use off-white
- âŒ **Just inverting colors**: Doesn't work properly â€” adjust lightness and saturation
- âŒ **High saturation** for large areas in dark mode: Creates visual vibration
- âŒ **Hue shift**: Don't change the hue of the light to dark mode

### 8.5. Accessibility Mistakes
- âŒ **Color-only indicators**: Don't use only color for status
- âŒ **Missing labels**: Don't rely on placeholder text
- âŒ **Disabled contrast**: Don't make disabled elements invisible
- âŒ **No focus indicators**: Don't remove focus outlines

